DIV2.P:
THE Senators, being convened in the Senate Chamber, in the city of Philadelphia, did, in the presence of William Bradford, one of the Judges of the Supreme Court of the commonwealth of Pennsylvania, swear or affirm "well and truly to try, and a true judgment give, according to law and evidence, between the commonwealth of Pennsylvania and John Nichol∣son, Comptroller General of the said commonwealth, on the articles of accu∣sation and impeachment exhibited against him the said John Nicholson, and now depending before the Senate," to wit,



